oneto follow unless there appears a clear reason for violating it: in any ,

a. But there are dependent indicative clauses in which this prin· ciple does not hold. The following are the most important.

1. After postquam, ubi, etc. (see 237), the perfect or historical present is regularly used. See also 235, a and 236, a.

2. After dum, while (see 234, a) the present is regularly used.
